                        <desc type="foundation">Although it is said to have been founded by
                                <roleName type="title">Saint</roleName>
                            <persName ref="PRS5365hirutaA">Ḫiruta ʾAmlāk</persName> (<date
                                notBefore="1200" notAfter="1299" precision="low">13th cent.</date>),
                            allegedly sent there by its spiritual father <roleName type="title"
                                >ʾabbā</roleName>
                            <persName ref="PRS5631IyasusM">ʾIyasus Moʾa</persName>, this is now believed to be a historical reconstruction linked to the attempts by the networks of 
                        </desc>
                        <ab type="history"/>
                        <ab type="tabot"><measure/></ab>
                        <ab type="description">The monastery of Dāgā ʾƎsṭifānos is located on the
                            small island of <placeName ref="LOC2419Daga">Dāgā</placeName>, on the
                            eastern side of the main island of <placeName ref="LOC2522Daq"
                                >Daq</placeName> at the centre of lake <placeName ref="LOC5888Tana"
                                >Ṭānā</placeName>. The history of the monastery and of its monks can
                            be broadly reconstructed thanks to its important library of manuscripts:
                                <num>67</num> were microfilmed by <persName ref="PRS5072Hammersc"
                                >Ernst Hammerschmidt</persName> and catalogued by Six; approx.
                                <num>40</num> were microfilmed by the <placeName ref="INS0332EMML"
                                >EMML</placeName> project and <num>28</num> are at the <placeName
                                ref="INS0303BNF">Bibliothèque Nationale de France</placeName>. </ab>
                    </note>
